Short:    HD-Installer for Addams Family V1.4
Author:   Codetapper/Action (codetapper@hotmail.com), ICQ: 26051687
Uploader: Codetapper/Action (codetapper@hotmail.com)
Version:  1.4
Type:     game/patch

This patch applies to "Addams Family" (c) 1992 Ocean - 1 disk.
Thanks to Carlo Pirri and Chris Vella for sending the originals!

REQUIREMENTS:
- Slave requires WHDLoad V10+.
- Game requires 512k chip mem and 512k other mem (+0.9Mb other memory 
  for preload option)

FEATURES:
- Full load from HD
- RNC copylock removed
- 1 access fault fixed
- Instructions included
- Trainer (Help to toggle infinite lives and Del to toggle energy. The
  screen will flash green when a cheat is enabled and red if disabled)
- 2 different RomIcons, NewIcons and GlowIcons (all created by Frank!)
- Quit option (default key is 'F10')

VERSION 1.4 BETA:
- OK I found a problem, caused by a copperlist getting corrupted after the
  operating system switched back to the game.

- I've disabled the extra 512k that it used
  (I think just for buffering files) and you can cut
  the diskimage down to $bb800 bytes.

- This config seems to allow you to preload the entire game on an
  A1200 without any fast memory, and even if some memory is used up,
  it loads from disk OK in my brief tests.

VERSION 1.3:
- Trainer flash screen code caused bugs in NTSC mode only. Thanks to
  Frank for the bug report!

CHEAT MODE:
- Taken from Sweet Cheater by Keith Krellwitz!
  Enter any of the following for your password:

            FIRST POWER-UP________________________"&1#1#"
            SECOND POWER-UP_______________________"?1S1M"
            THIRD POWER-UP________________________"BLSRS"
            PUGSLEY_______________________________"V121B"
            WEDNESDAY_____________________________"VD2RL"
            GRANNY________________________________"V&YKW"
            FESTER________________________________"VL#R4"
            GAME ENDING___________________________"#Z6D?"

  To get 4 free lives each time your game is over, walk past the continue
  door to the left and there is a room where you can collect them.
  
  In the hall of rooms, walk left until there is a door above you.
  Push up to enter a secret room; collect all the stuff in this room
  and go directly above where you entered this room and press up to
  enter the other secret room.

  On some versions of the game enter the code `11111' on the password
  screen for 100 lives.

  For Morticia, use the 3rd power-up code, go to the piano room and
  wait for the Addams Family music to play.  Now open the self sealed
  door and finish the last level.

  Pause the game by pressing 'SPACE' and then hit the 'ESC' key.  You
  will now be in a room with a continue door and an escape door.
  Instead of choosing one of these options just keep walking left
  until you come across another room full of extra lives.


The trainer in this game was done the old fashioned way, play the game and
quit with 5 lives making a dump of memory. Then play again with 4 lives 
and do a diff on the files! Search for all memory accesses to that location
and bingo!

I couldn't decide which icon I liked better so I have included all of them
in the installer. I suggest you rename the icons and have a look to decide
which you like better!

Currently there is one illegal copperlist entry in the game which I have
been unsuccessful at skipping so far so if you are desperate to rip 
pictures, use WHDLoad 12 as it will not complain. Be aware that the game
runs perfectly with it so do not fear!

Greetings to Jean-François Fabre for the original version, Mr Larmer for
Copylock Decoder, Bored Seal for testing and bug reports, Galahad/Fairlight
for testing and copperlist advice, Bert for constantly improving WHDLoad,
Carlo and Chris for being the best original suppliers ever, Frank for 
awesome icons and finally all Action members!


